race.comment: BERRY BERRY GOOD (1) showed good early speed last start before fading in the stretch over 1000m at Moora. He'd won comfortably at Mt Magnet prior and has a handy 2kg claim. Will be prominent from the outset and he can bounce back in this lineup. SHASFA (3) is building towards a win with placings at her last two runs. The shorter sprint suits as well as the low gate which she will use. CITY MISTRESS (4) finally draws an inside gate and hasn't been too far away at York the latest and Toodyay. This suits better and she's had a switch of yards. Keep safe. DEAL OBTAINED (5) is hard to catch but would get some of the money if he found his A-game.
